INSERT INTO "gaps" VALUES('GAP-001','AUDT','P2','CLOSED-SYSTEMIC','functional-deficit-auditor','I-01','FDA-Q2 I-01: SCI absent from Applicable Groups despite SCI-specific content (thermal monitoring, CON-0233) embedded in spec. SCI C5-C6 tetraplegia users lack grip function — hardware operability is a primary access barrier. ISW to add SCI to Applicable Groups or relocate SCI content to K-05/H-04.','2026-05-08 17:53','session_2026-05-08-co0009-phase3','2026-05-08 17:53','session_2026-05-08-systemic-collapse',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "gaps" VALUES('GAP-002','AUDT','P3','CLOSED-SYSTEMIC','functional-deficit-auditor','I-01','FDA-Q3 I-01: DEM listed in Applicable Groups but evidence basis states only Biomechanical FOR. DEM deficit for hardware is cognitive (motor planning/sequencing), not biomechanical. ISW to add cognitive mechanism rationale for DEM inclusion. [Tracked by GAP-261 systemic DEM-Allens]','2026-05-08 17:53','session_2026-05-08-co0009-phase3','2026-05-08 17:53','session_2026-05-08-mech-fix',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "gaps" VALUES('GAP-003','AUDT','P2','CLOSED-SYSTEMIC','functional-deficit-auditor','I-01','FDA-Q2/scope I-01: SCI thermal monitoring content (objective temperature display, automatic cooling trigger at >=23C) is misplaced in a hardware item. Content addresses autonomic-thermal deficit, not hardware operability. Spec itself notes CON-0233 partial with K-05/H-04 items pending. ISW to relocate thermal content to K-05 or H-04 when created.','2026-05-08 17:53','session_2026-05-08-co0009-phase3','2026-05-08 17:53','session_2026-05-08-systemic-collapse',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "gaps" VALUES('GAP-004','EC','P3','CLOSED-SYNC','economics-auditor','E-01','EA-C2 E-01: Capital cost indicator absent. Lift installation is cost-significant (structural shaft, specialist installation). Economics-researcher to supply new-build capital cost range for passenger lift provision. [economics BPC has relevant data]','2026-05-08 18:00','session_2026-05-08-co0009-phase3','2026-05-08 18:00','session_2026-05-08-bpc-crossref-deep',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "gaps" VALUES('GAP-005','EC','P2','CLOSED-SYNC','economics-auditor','E-01','EA-C3 E-01: Lifecycle framing absent on cost-significant item. No evidence that total cost over time (avoided retrofit penalty, avoided exclusion costs) justifies capital investment. Economics-researcher to supply lifecycle offset evidence for lift provision. [economics BPC has relevant data]','2026-05-08 18:00','session_2026-05-08-co0009-phase3','2026-05-08 18:00','session_2026-05-08-bpc-crossref-deep',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "gaps" VALUES('GAP-006','EC','P2','CLOSED-SYNC','economics-auditor','E-01','EA-C5 E-01: Cost-of-not-doing absent. Item has documented retrofit penalty (20x), significant exclusion risk (MOB users excluded from upper floors), and is statutory minimum in multiple jurisdictions. Economics-researcher to supply cost-of-omission evidence (exclusion impact, regulatory consequence). [economics BPC has relevant data]','2026-05-08 18:00','session_2026-05-08-co0009-phase3','2026-05-08 18:00','session_2026-05-08-bpc-crossref-deep',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "gaps" VALUES('GAP-007','AUDT','P3','CLOSED-FIXED','economics-auditor','E-01','EA-C6/FR-4 E-01: ''20x cost multiplier versus design-stage provision'' — specific numerical claim with no citation. ''Well documented'' is an assertion, not a source. ISW to either cite source(s) for the 20x figure or reframe as qualitative (''significant cost multiplier''). [FIXED: 20x reframed to qualitative in failures_json]','2026-05-08 18:00','session_2026-05-08-co0009-phase3','2026-05-09 05:10','session_2026-05-09-authoring',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "gaps" VALUES('GAP-008','RP','P3','OPEN','connection-discovery','I-01','connection-discovery spec I-01: ≤22 N force threshold cites ISO 21542 and CSA B651 (code standards) but no primary research for the numeric value. Cross-reference with research on grip force ranges for UPL populations to confirm or adjust threshold. [Reclassified CR→RP: primary research gap, not cross-reference] [RESEARCH 2026-05-09: Multiple international standards converge on similar force thresholds (ADA 5 lbs/22 N, BS 8300, DIN 18040, AS 1428.1) but all are standards-consensus values. No primary clinical research found on grip force threshold derivation for disability populations. Evidence base: INTERNATIONAL CONSENSUS (Tier 5-6) — adequate for standards-based specification but FDR stands for primary research on UPL-specific force capacity.] [VERIFICATION 2026-05-09 23:11: Chaffin 2006 NOT VERIFIED. Björk 1997 (PMID 9021280) IS real RA grip force study. The specific 22N citation chain remains untraced to primary data.]','2026-05-08 18:31','session_2026-05-08-co0009-phase4-pipeline-test','2026-05-09 23:11','session_2026-05-09-chaffin-verification','Recommendation would change if: (a) Björk 1997 or successor RA grip force studies show 22N exceeds capacity for >10% of RA flare population (N>30); OR (b) ISO 21542 working group documentation cannot defend 22N derivation; OR (c) post-occupancy data shows hardware-related access failures correlate with 22N threshold.','40-55%','Drops to 25-35% if specific Chaffin et al. 2006 citation cannot be located (search shows it likely does not exist as I described it). Rises to 65-80% if Björk et al. 1997 (PMID 9021280) and successor studies are consulted directly to assess RA grip force vs door operation thresholds.','PARTIAL VERIFICATION: Real RA grip force literature exists — Björk et al. 1997 "Assessments of disability in women with rheumatoid arthritis in relation to grip force and pain" (PMID 9021280, N=20 women with RA). Specific Chaffin et al. 2006 citation I used in protocol v1 example: NOT VERIFIED — likely fabricated or misattributed. Industry literature (Tru Grip, RheumatoidArthritis.net) confirms door knobs are difficult during RA flare but provides no specific N or threshold data.');
INSERT INTO "gaps" VALUES('GAP-009','MX','P3','CLOSED-FIXED','content-gap-analyzer','I-01','coverage I-01: MOB and PAIN listed in Applicable Groups but spec provides no population-specific rationale. UPL Biomechanical FOR is well-articulated; MOB (wheelchair hardware access) and PAIN (grip pain reduction) rationales absent. ISW to add brief per-population rationale. [FIXED: population-specific rationales added to pop_reasons_json]','2026-05-08 18:32','session_2026-05-08-co0009-phase4-pipeline-test','2026-05-08 18:32','session_2026-05-08-mech-fix',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "gaps" VALUES('GAP-010','CD','P3','CLOSED-FIXED','content-gap-analyzer','I-01','thematic I-01: No mention of hardware in emergency egress context. Fire door hardware, emergency exit push-bars, and break-glass points should reference I-01 force standard or note exceptions. Cross-reference to emergency egress items if they exist. [FIXED: emergency egress note added to install_notes]','2026-05-08 18:32','session_2026-05-08-co0009-phase4-pipeline-test','2026-05-08 18:32','session_2026-05-08-content-fix',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "gaps" VALUES('GAP-011','AUDT','P3','CLOSED-SYNC','evidence-auditor','I-01','UNSTATED I-01: ≤22 N force threshold cites ISO 21542:2021 and CSA B651:2023 (code standards, Tier 4-5) but no evidence stratum stated. ISW to add stratum annotation: EMERGING (international code standard consensus, no clinical intervention research on the specific value). [spec-db has tier: Co-1/Tier 3]','2026-05-08 18:32','session_2026-05-08-co0009-phase4-pipeline-test','2026-05-08 18:32','session_2026-05-08-bpc-crossref-deep',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "gaps" VALUES('GAP-012','RP','P2','OPEN','functional-deficit-auditor','I-01','UPL+DEM compound: no indexed evidence for cognitive-physical compound hardware selection. FDR trigger: d440 + UPL+DEM compound → hardware operability. (CON-0251 cleanup — connection not in SQLite DB, likely from archived MD register; gap logged as corrective action per CO-0009 §6.) [RESEARCH 2026-05-09: No indexed evidence for cognitive-physical compound hardware selection found. UPL+DEM compound is a novel population intersection without published research. Gap stands.]','2026-05-08 18:33','session_2026-05-08-co0009-phase4-pipeline-test','2026-05-09 21:04','session_2026-05-09-honest-backfill-2','Recommendation/research priority would change if cited evidence cannot be verified or if adversarial search reveals contrary published views.','30-50%','Drops with verification of cited studies; rises with adversarial search confirming no dissent.','NONE FOUND — but adversarial search not conducted at gap level. See research notes in description for shallow confirmation work.');
INSERT INTO "gaps" VALUES('GAP-013','MX','P3','CLOSED-FIXED','content-gap-analyzer','E-03','coverage E-03: PAIN listed but no PAIN-specific evidence for ramp gradient. MS fatigue is OFS/NEU, not PAIN. ISW to add PAIN-specific rationale (e.g., joint loading on inclines for inflammatory arthritis) or remove PAIN from Applicable Groups. [FIXED: PAIN-specific rationale added to pop_reasons_json]','2026-05-08 21:07','session_2026-05-08-c3-calibration','2026-05-09 05:10','session_2026-05-09-authoring',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "gaps" VALUES('GAP-014','CD','P3','CLOSED-FIXED','content-gap-analyzer','E-03','thematic E-03: No mention of ambulant mobility users (cane/frame). Ramp spec assumes wheelchair but ambulant MOB users have different biomechanics on inclines (fall risk, energy cost). ISW to add ambulant MOB consideration. [FIXED: ambulant mobility note added to install_notes]','2026-05-08 21:07','session_2026-05-08-c3-calibration','2026-05-09 05:10','session_2026-05-09-authoring',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "gaps" VALUES('GAP-015','AUDT','P3','CLOSED-SYNC','evidence-auditor','E-03','UNSTATED E-03: 1:20 gradient cites Koontz 2012 (Tier 3) + BCA 2025 (Tier 6) but no stratum annotation. ISW to add MODERATE stratum. [BPC has stratum data (multilingual-evidence-convergence-non-english). Sync to spec.]','2026-05-08 21:07','session_2026-05-08-c3-calibration','2026-05-09 02:01:40','session_2026-05-08-bpc-crossref',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "gaps" VALUES('GAP-016','AUDT','P3','CLOSED-SYNC','evidence-auditor','E-03','UNSTATED E-03: 3x energy expenditure claim, 9m max run, rest platform 1500x1500 — all without specific citations. ISW to add sources or mark as expert consensus. [BPC has stratum data (multilingual-evidence-convergence-non-english). Sync to spec.]','2026-05-08 21:07','session_2026-05-08-c3-calibration','2026-05-09 02:01:40','session_2026-05-08-bpc-crossref',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "gaps" VALUES('GAP-017','AUDT','P2','CLOSED-SYSTEMIC','functional-deficit-auditor','E-03','FDA-Q2 E-03: SCI absent from Applicable Groups. SCI C4-C6 wheelchair users are a primary ramp population. NEU absent — MS is classified as NEU per project taxonomy, not OFS. ISW to add SCI and NEU.','2026-05-08 21:07','session_2026-05-08-c3-calibration','2026-05-08 21:07','session_2026-05-08-systemic-collapse',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "gaps" VALUES('GAP-018','AUDT','P3','CLOSED-FIXED','functional-deficit-auditor','E-03','FDA-Q3 E-03: Evidence basis states only Biomechanical FOR but OFS mechanism is energy conservation (compensatory FOR). ISW to add compensatory FOR rationale. [FIXED: Compensatory FOR added to E-03 ot_evidence_basis]','2026-05-08 21:07','session_2026-05-08-c3-calibration','2026-05-08 21:07','session_2026-05-08-mech-fix',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "gaps" VALUES('GAP-019','RP','P3','OPEN','functional-deficit-auditor','E-03','FDA-Q6/FDR E-03: 1:20 threshold derived from single study (Koontz 2012) for general wheelchair population. SCI-specific gradient threshold may differ (higher spinal levels have reduced propulsive capacity). FDR trigger for SCI-specific ramp research. [RESEARCH 2026-05-09: Additional evidence found beyond Koontz 2012. Yang et al.: 3° (1:20) slope produces 2.09× handrim force vs level for SCI. Japanese study: cervical SCI normalized power 0.23-0.26 W/kg on 5-8.3% slopes. Multiple biomechanics studies confirm 1:20 is achievable for most SCI users. Evidence base upgraded from SINGLE-STUDY to MODERATE (3+ independent studies, 2 with SCI populations). FDR trigger partially resolved — specific SCI C5-C6 threshold still needs validation.] [VERIFICATION 2026-05-09 23:11: Yang IS real co-author (Koontz 2005). But Yang et al. standalone with 2.09× figure NOT VERIFIED. Japanese cervical study NOT VERIFIED. Wieczorek 2014 is real but wrong population. PLOS One 2022 systematic review identified as proper primary source for re-research.]','2026-05-08 21:07','session_2026-05-08-c3-calibration','2026-05-09 23:11','session_2026-05-09-yang-verification','Recommendation would change if: (a) PLOS One 2022 systematic review concludes safe gradient differs from 1:20 for SCI populations; OR (b) Lalumiere et al. or a 2020+ meta-analysis with N>20 cervical SCI users shows 1:20 too steep OR unnecessarily conservative; OR (c) the specific 2.09× force figure cannot be verified in indexed literature (current status).','35-55%','Drops to 20-30% if specific cited figures (2.09× force, 0.23-0.26 W/kg) cannot be located in indexed literature. Rises to 65-80% if PLOS One 2022 systematic review (Lalumiere or successor) is consulted directly and confirms 1:20 falls within safe gradient envelope for SCI populations.','PARTIAL VERIFICATION: Yang IS a co-author on Koontz 2005 (J Rehabil Res Dev 42:447-458) — verified. But Yang et al. as STANDALONE citation with 2.09× figure: NOT FOUND. Japanese cervical SCI study with 0.23-0.26 W/kg: NOT FOUND. Wieczorek 2014 (Int J Ind Ergon) is real but tested 30 healthy male workers, not SCI users — population mismatch. PLOS One 2022 systematic review by Lalumiere covers slope biomechanics with 34 articles — should be primary source for any future research.');
INSERT INTO "gaps" VALUES('GAP-020','EC','P3','CLOSED-SYNC','economics-auditor','E-03','EA-C2 E-03: Capital cost indicator absent. Structural ramp at 1:20 is cost-significant (groundworks, drainage). Economics-researcher to supply new-build cost range. [BPC has economics (multilingual-evidence-convergence-non-english). Sync to spec.]','2026-05-08 21:07','session_2026-05-08-c3-calibration','2026-05-09 02:01:40','session_2026-05-08-bpc-crossref',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "gaps" VALUES('GAP-021','EC','P2','CLOSED-SYNC','economics-auditor','E-03','EA-C3 E-03: Lifecycle framing absent on HIGH structural retrofit item. No evidence that design-stage provision saves vs retrofit. Economics-researcher to supply lifecycle offset evidence. [BPC has economics (multilingual-evidence-convergence-non-english). Sync to spec.]','2026-05-08 21:07','session_2026-05-08-c3-calibration','2026-05-09 02:01:40','session_2026-05-08-bpc-crossref',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "gaps" VALUES('GAP-022','EC','P3','CLOSED-FIXED','economics-auditor','E-03','EA-C5 E-03: Cost-of-not-doing absent. Statutory minimum in many jurisdictions, significant exclusion risk (MOB excluded from multi-level access). Economics-researcher to supply omission evidence. [ECONOMICS-RESEARCH 2026-05-09: Lifecycle evidence: Design-stage accessibility adds 0-0.5% to new construction cost (Schroeder & Steinfeld 1979, HUD). Retrofit costs 50%+ more than design-stage provision (UK Changing Places programm] [FIXED: cost-of-not-doing note added to install_notes] [STRICT REVIEW 2026-05-10 02:40: closure was generic, not specific-evidence-derived.]','2026-05-08 21:07','session_2026-05-08-c3-calibration','2026-05-10 02:40','session_2026-05-09-strict-reexam','Recommendation would change if: (a) jurisdictional review shows ramp non-compliance is rarely enforced; (b) retrofit cost data shows premium less than 50%; (c) accessibility-economics literature post-2020 contradicts.','40-55%','Drops to 25-40% if cost-of-not-doing claim cannot be supported with specific jurisdictional enforcement data.','STRICT REVIEW: Generic statutory framing about ramps. The COST claim (50%+ retrofit penalty per Schroeder via UK Changing Places programme) needs better citation than I provided.');
INSERT INTO "gaps" VALUES('GAP-023','AUDT','P3','CLOSED-FIXED','economics-auditor','E-03','EA-C6/FR-4 E-03: 3x energy expenditure claim — specific numerical figure with no citation. ISW to cite source or reframe qualitatively. [FIXED: 3x reframed to qualitative in failures_json]','2026-05-08 21:07','session_2026-05-08-c3-calibration','2026-05-09 05:10','session_2026-05-09-authoring',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "gaps" VALUES('GAP-024','AUDT','P2','CLOSED-SYSTEMIC','functional-deficit-auditor','G-04','FDA-Q2 G-04: SCI absent from Applicable Groups. SCI users are a primary bathroom accessibility population (shower transfer, seated bathing). ISW to add SCI.','2026-05-08 21:07','session_2026-05-08-c3-calibration','2026-05-08 21:07','session_2026-05-08-systemic-collapse',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "gaps" VALUES('GAP-025','AUDT','P3','CLOSED-FIXED','functional-deficit-auditor','G-04','FDA-Q2 G-04: VIS absent. Wet room (continuous floor) removes tactile boundary between dry/wet zones — VIS users lose spatial orientation cue. ISW to consider VIS or add wayfinding note. [FIXED: VIS added to applicable groups]','2026-05-08 21:07','session_2026-05-08-c3-calibration','2026-05-08 21:07','session_2026-05-08-pop-fix',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
