INSERT INTO "gaps" VALUES('GAP-074','RP','P2','OPEN','content-gap-analyzer','A-11','THIN-BASE A-11: Item has THIN BASE flag. FDR trigger for targeted literature review. [RESEARCH 2026-05-09: Room Perimeter Hearing Loop — same evidence base as A-10. IEC 60118-4, BS 8300, PMC efficacy study. Well-evidenced technology. BPC=YES] [STRICT REVIEW 2026-05-10 02:40: same pattern as GAP-069.]','2026-05-09 01:43','session_2026-05-08-c3-batch-a','2026-05-10 02:40','session_2026-05-09-strict-reexam','Same as GAP-069 — would change with comparative-placement study or supersession.','40-55%','Same pattern as GAP-069. IEC 60118-4 specifies performance not placement. Room-perimeter installation is design choice.','STRICT REVIEW: same as GAP-069. Standard specifies HOW loops perform; the "perimeter loop in assembly spaces" is a design pattern, not an evidence-derived requirement.');
INSERT INTO "gaps" VALUES('GAP-075','AUDT','P3','CLOSED-SYNC','evidence-auditor','A-12','UNSTATED A-12: 1 numerical specification(s) without evidence stratum annotation. ISW to add stratum per project-standards. [BPC has stratum data (assistive-listening-systems). Sync to spec.]','2026-05-09 01:43','session_2026-05-08-c3-batch-a','2026-05-09 02:01:40','session_2026-05-08-bpc-crossref',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "gaps" VALUES('GAP-076','RP','P3','OPEN','content-gap-analyzer','A-12','THIN-BASE A-12: Item has THIN BASE flag. FDR trigger for targeted literature review. [RESEARCH 2026-05-09: Auracast Infrastructure — Bluetooth LE Audio standard (2022), emerging technology. THIN BASE legitimate — limited built environment implementation evidence.] [VERIFIED: Auracast deployment well-evidenced (REF-VERIFIED-008). UK rollout active.] [STRICT REVIEW 2026-05-10 02:40: Auracast is real, but "specify readiness now" is forward-looking design decision. Confidence reduced from 70-85% to 50-65%. REOPENED.]','2026-05-09 01:43','session_2026-05-08-c3-batch-a','2026-05-10 02:40','session_2026-05-09-strict-reexam','Recommendation would change if: (a) Auracast adoption rate falls below ABI forecast; (b) NHS or major hearing aid maker stops integration; (c) competing standard achieves dominant market share; (d) study shows building-side readiness specification adds no value vs retrofit-when-needed.','50-65%','Drops to 35-50% if Auracast adoption stalls or NHS/major hearing aid makers fail to integrate. Rises to 70-85% with sustained deployment growth and confirmed ABI forecast realization.','STRICT REVIEW: Auracast IS real and deploying, but "specify Auracast readiness in new buildings" is a forward-looking infrastructure choice, not directly evidence-derived. The deployment evidence (Bristol Temple Meads, Sydney Opera, etc.) demonstrates feasibility, NOT that specifying readiness in 2026 vs 2030 is required. The 2.5M global deployment forecast is INDUSTRY projection, not empirical study of building-readiness benefit.');
