INSERT INTO "gaps" VALUES('GAP-097','RP','P3','OPEN','functional-deficit-auditor','B-02','THIN-BASE B-02: Item has THIN BASE flag. FDR trigger for targeted literature review. [RESEARCH 2026-05-09: Diffuse Lighting for Lip Reading — speech intelligibility research exists (PMC, audiological literature) but specific lux levels for lip-reading shadow-free illumination may be thin.] [ADVERSARIAL 2026-05-09: Searched BS 8300:2018, CIBSE lighting guides, PubMed audiological literature, AJA lipreading review (Bernstein et al. 2021). No published lux threshold for lip-reading-specific illumination found in any built environment standard. Qualitative guidance only: well-lit, shadow-free, face visible. THIN BASE CONFIRMED — gap stands.] [VERIFIED: Erber 1974 (REF-VERIFIED-009) provides empirical basis for shadow-free face illumination.] [REVISED 2026-05-09 23:38: Owner cross-check confirmed Erber shows shadow effect but NO standard provides quantitative lux thresholds for lipreading. My closure premature.]','2026-05-09 01:45','session_2026-05-08-c3-batch-all','2026-05-09 23:38','session_2026-05-09-cross-check-revision','Recommendation would change if: (a) B-02 lux thresholds derive from non-lipreading-specific lighting research and that fact is documented; (b) successor study provides quantitative dose-response for lipreading lighting; (c) specific lux levels in B-02 prove to be project-specific interpretation rather than evidence-derived.','25-40%','Drops to 15-25% if specific lux thresholds in B-02 cannot be matched to ANY published evidence. Rises to 50-65% if quantitative dose-response studies emerge for lipreading-specific illumination.','Owner spot-check: BS 8300:2018, CIBSE lighting guides, PubMed audiological literature, AJA Bernstein 2021 review — NO published lux threshold for lip-reading-specific illumination in any built environment standard. Erber 1974 shows shadow effect (3-12%) but does NOT provide quantitative lux thresholds. Specific lux levels in B-02 may be unsupported.');
