INSERT INTO "search_languages" VALUES('stair-ramp-threshold-biomechanics-accessibility','DE','SEARCHED',8,'TIER2 NATIVE SEARCH 2026-05-11. KEY INSTRUMENT: DIN 18040-1 (public buildings), DIN 18040-2 (housing). RAMP GRADIENT: maximum 6% (1:16.67) for self-propelled manual wheelchair users in public buildings; exception ≤10% for short ramps (up to 3m length). Cross-fall: 0% required (rollover risk). Resting platforms: required every 6m; 1.50m×1.50m at start and end. Minimum width: 1.20m. THRESHOLD: schwellenlos concept — standard practice ≤2mm height difference at level access points; DIN 18040-1 requires level (niveaufreier) access. CRITICAL DIVERGENCE from EN/UK (Approved Document M): DE maximum is 6% (1:16.67) for all lengths vs UK''s length-tiered table (1:20 for 10m, 1:15 for 5m, 1:12 for 2m — UK permits steeper gradient for short runs). DE exception (10% for ≤3m) vs UK steepest 1:12 (8.33%) — these do not align: DE allows steeper exception than UK long-run limit but stricter than UK''s steepest allowed. CRITICAL DIVERGENCE from ADA: ADA universal 1:12 (8.33%) is steeper than DE''s 6% general requirement. Source: nullbarriere.de (DIN 18040-1 rampen), auffahrrampen-thiele.de. CONFIDENCE: high for gradient values; medium for threshold mm-value (≤2mm practice confirmed from broader DE barrier-free knowledge, not retrieved directly this session).','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-11T02:38:32.334911+00:00','session_2026-05-11a-tier2-multilingual');
INSERT INTO "search_languages" VALUES('stair-ramp-threshold-biomechanics-accessibility','FR','SEARCHED',9,'TIER2 NATIVE SEARCH 2026-05-11. KEY INSTRUMENTS: Loi n° 2005-102 du 11 février 2005, Arrêté du 1er août 2006 (ERP neufs), Arrêté du 8 décembre 2014 and Arrêté du 20 avril 2017 (ERP existants). RAMP GRADIENT — NEW ERP (bâti neuf): Standard ≤5% (general); Tolerance ≤8% for ≤2m run; Exceptional ≤10% for ≤0.5m run. Rest platforms every 10m, minimum 1.40×1.20m. Min width 1.20m; turning space Ø1.50m. NEW ERP EXISTING (bâti existant): Standard ≤6%; Tolerance ≤10% for ≤2m; Exceptional ≤12% for ≤0.5m. CRITICAL DIVERGENCES: (1) FR new ERP standard ≤5% aligns with DA (1:20) and FI (1:20) — among the most restrictive for standard runs. (2) FR uses a LENGTH-TIERED table (like UK, ES) but with different breakpoints — 2m/0.5m thresholds vs UK 5m/2m, ES 3m/6m tiers. (3) FR distinguishes new vs existing buildings (like IT for new vs retrofit) — a design philosophy shared with UK (existing exceptions) but not with DA/FI (single standard, no retrofit exception). (4) For existing buildings, FR''s standard ≤6% matches DE''s general new-construction mandatory. Sources: axsol.fr/pente-rampe-pmr, mon-erp.fr/rampe-pmr, oui-adapt.fr, handinorme.com/rampes. CONFIDENCE: high — multiple practitioner sources citing Arrêtés de 2006/2014 directly.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-11T03:15:46.948011+00:00','session_2026-05-11d-tier2-final');
INSERT INTO "search_languages" VALUES('stair-ramp-threshold-biomechanics-accessibility','DA','SEARCHED',8,'TIER2 NATIVE SEARCH 2026-05-11. KEY INSTRUMENT: BR18 (Bygningsreglementet 2018) §49 (common access routes) and §56 (public buildings). Supporting: DS 3028:2001 (Tilgængelighed for alle). RAMP GRADIENT: Maximum ≤1:20 (5%, 50mm/m) — single mandatory maximum for wheelchair-accessible ramps; NO short-run exception. Resting platforms required every 12m if gradient exceeds 1:25 (4%). Minimum width ≥1.3m. Platforms 1.3×1.3m at each end. Handrails both sides; not required for gradients ≤1:25. Cross-fall guidance: ≤1:40 recommended. EXCEPTION: curb ramps (kantstensrampe) may use 1:10. CRITICAL DIVERGENCE: (1) DA ≤1:20 (5%) is the MOST RESTRICTIVE single mandatory maximum in the comparison — stricter than DE 6%, NO 1:15 (6.7%), SV binding 1:12 (8.33%), JA/ZH 1:12, ADA 1:12, ES 12%/8%/6% tiered. Only equivalent is UK''s long-run (10m) preferred 1:20. (2) DA has NO short-run exception — unlike UK (1:12 for ≤2m), DE (10% for ≤3m), ES (12% for ≤3m). (3) DA''s mandatory 1:20 is stricter than both DE general (6%) and NO general (1:15). Sources: bygningsreglementet.dk §49-56, weland.dk/projektering (BR18 citations), tilgaengelighed.km.dk/anvisning. CONFIDENCE: high — primary BR18 article text and multiple practitioner sources confirm ≤1:20 from the regulation directly.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-11T03:00:55.299316+00:00','session_2026-05-11c-tier2-continued');
INSERT INTO "search_languages" VALUES('stair-ramp-threshold-biomechanics-accessibility','FI','SEARCHED',9,'TIER2 NATIVE SEARCH 2026-05-11. KEY INSTRUMENTS: Asetus rakennuksen esteettömyydestä (Decree on Building Accessibility, Ympäristöministeriö / Ministry of the Environment) — Decree 241/2017 confirmed by YM guidance 2018 (Ohje esteettömyys 2018). RAMP GRADIENT: Maximum ≤5% (1:20) — mandatory. Exception: if total height difference ≤1000mm, gradient may be ≤8% (1:12.5); in that case, continuous ramp rise ≤500mm followed by ≥2000mm level platform (välitasanne). Outdoor ramps: gradient >5% permitted only if maintained to indoor standard (e.g. covered or kept ice-free). Width ≥900mm (single lane). Platforms ≥1500mm at top and bottom. Guard edge ≥50mm if ramp not bounded by fixed structure. CRITICAL DIVERGENCES: (1) FI ≤5% (1:20) mandatory maximum aligns with DA (BR18 ≤1:20) — both are the MOST RESTRICTIVE mandatory values in the comparison. (2) FI exception (≤8% for h≤1000mm in 500mm segments) is similar in structure to JA (≤1/8 for h≤16cm) but with different height/length limits. (3) FI is stricter than DE (6% general), NO (1:15 = 6.7%), ES (12% for ≤3m), JA/ZH/ADA (1:12 = 8.33%). (4) Like DA, FI has NO short-run steeper exception for typical building access — unlike UK (1:12 for ≤2m). Sources: ym.fi/Ohje_esteettomyys_2018 (primary decree guidance), valtioneuvosto.fi/Kilpela_esteettomyysasetus, invalidiliitto.fi/esteettomyys/luiska, Helsinki urban space guide. CONFIDENCE: high — multiple Finnish authoritative sources citing Decree 241/2017 directly.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-11T03:05:48.017086+00:00','session_2026-05-11c-tier2-continued');
INSERT INTO "search_languages" VALUES('stair-ramp-threshold-biomechanics-accessibility','EN','SEARCHED',10,'TIER2 NATIVE SEARCH 2026-05-11. KEY INSTRUMENTS: UK — Approved Document M (Part M Building Regulations, legally binding), BS 8300-1:2018. ADA (US) — ADA Standards for Accessible Design. RAMP GRADIENT UK: Length-tiered table in Approved Document M Table 1 — 1:20 for ≤10m going (max 500mm rise), 1:15 for ≤5m going (max 333mm rise), 1:12 for ≤2m going. Gradient 1:20 is shallowest/longest; 1:12 is steepest/shortest. Slopes 1:20–1:60: rest landings every 500mm rise (per BS8300:2009). Maximum gradient 1:12. THRESHOLD: abutting surfaces max 3mm height difference (Approved Document M). RAMP GRADIENT US/ADA: single maximum 1:12 (8.33%) — no length differentiation in primary requirement. CRITICAL DIVERGENCE: UK uses length-tiered gradient table (most jurisdictions do not — they pick a single maximum); UK preferred long-run gradient 1:20 = 5% is stricter than ADA 1:12 and equal to NO preferred, but stricter than DE''s 6% general limit. Any batch synthesis claiming "1:12 maximum" is correct for ADA but wrong for UK long runs (which must be 1:20). Sources: Approved Document M Vol 2 (2024 amendments), BS 8300:2009 update, rapidramp.co.uk (citing Part M). CONFIDENCE: high — Approved Document M table values confirmed from official government document.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-11T02:38:32.334911+00:00','session_2026-05-11a-tier2-multilingual');
INSERT INTO "search_languages" VALUES('stair-ramp-threshold-biomechanics-accessibility','ES','SEARCHED',5,'TIER2 BONUS FINDING 2026-05-11 (from luminance-contrast ES search). KEY INSTRUMENT: CTE DB SUA 9 (Código Técnico de la Edificación). RAMP GRADIENT: Length-tiered table: ≤12% for ≤3m, ≤8% for 3-6m (some sources say 3-6m at 8%), ≤6% for 6-9m, ≤4% for exceptional/long ramps. Cross-fall: ≤2%. CRITICAL DIVERGENCE: ES uses a third distinct length-tiered table different from both UK (1:20/1:15/1:12) and DE (single 6%/10%exception). ES allows steeper 12% for very short runs (vs UK max 1:12=8.33% and DE max exception 10%). ES 8% for 3-6m is stricter than DE''s 6% general? No — DE 6% = 6%, ES 8% at 3-6m = less strict. Comparison: ES 12% short run > DE exception 10% > UK 1:12 (8.33%). This is another jurisdictional divergence batch synthesis would miss. Note: this was found incidentally; ES luminance contrast search did not find ramp-specific sources. Sources: verificacioncte.es, vitoria-gasteiz.org/dbsua-criteria. CONFIDENCE: high for CTE DB SUA gradient table values.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-11T02:53:14.624085+00:00','session_2026-05-11b-tier2-continued');
INSERT INTO "search_languages" VALUES('stair-ramp-threshold-biomechanics-accessibility','ZH','SEARCHED',9,'TIER2 NATIVE SEARCH 2026-05-11. KEY INSTRUMENT: GB 50763-2012《无障碍设计规范》(Accessibility Design Code, Ministry of Housing and Urban-Rural Development, effective 2012-09-01). RAMP GRADIENT: §3.4 轮椅坡道 (wheelchair ramps): Maximum ≤1:12 (8.33%) — mandatory. Table 3.4.4 (最大高度和水平长度): tiered table of maximum height and horizontal length for each gradient, providing additional constraints. Flat entrance (平坡出入口): ≤1:20 (5%), preferred ≤1:30 (3.3%). Handrails required when height >300mm AND gradient >1:20. Outdoor paths in parks: main path <5% (1:20); mountain parks <8%; secondary paths <8%; bridges <8% for no wheelchair access. THRESHOLD: not explicitly specified as a number in §3.3 — level transitions >15mm need to be addressed (implied from general accessible route provisions). CRITICAL DIVERGENCE: (1) ZH uses single mandatory max (1:12), NOT length-tiered table like UK. (2) ZH mandatory 1:12 (8.33%) is LESS strict than DE''s 6% (1:16.67): ZH allows steeper standard ramps than DE. (3) ZH preferred for flat entrances (1:20) matches UK long-run requirement but is a different element type context. (4) Table 3.4.4 adds height/length constraints by gradient — provides some UK-like differentiation but structured differently. Sources: GB 50763-2012 §3.4 full text (ahsz.gov.cn, bzko.com), soujianzhu.cn normalized version, Zhihu annotation, Shenzhen local standard reinforcing GB values. CONFIDENCE: high — direct GB 50763-2012 article text retrieved from multiple sources.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-11T02:55:46.554597+00:00','session_2026-05-11b-tier2-continued');
INSERT INTO "search_languages" VALUES('stair-ramp-threshold-biomechanics-accessibility','IT','SEARCHED',8,'TIER2 NATIVE SEARCH 2026-05-11. KEY INSTRUMENTS: DM 236/1989 (Decreto Ministeriale 236/1989, Ministero dei Lavori Pubblici) — primary accessibility regulation for private buildings (legge 13/1989); DPR 503/1996 — public buildings and spaces; UNI CEI EN 17210:2021 (accessible design guideline). RAMP GRADIENT: New construction: max 8% (1:12.5); Adeguamento (existing buildings retrofit): up to 12% for short runs (with run-length restrictions); Short street-level connections (raccordo con livello stradale): up to 15% for height ≤15cm. Recommended outdoor: 5-6%. Platforms every 10m. Max height difference via ramps only: 3.20m (above which lifts/stairs required). Min width 0.90m single pass, 1.50m at platforms. CRITICAL DIVERGENCES: (1) IT 8% (1:12.5) is close to but slightly stricter than JA/ZH/ADA (1:12 = 8.33%). (2) IT uses a single maximum value for new construction (no length-tiered table like UK or ES). (3) IT is LESS strict than DA/FI (5%), DE (6%), NO (6.7%) — allows steeper new-build ramps. (4) IT retrofit exception (up to 12%) parallels ES short-run (12% for ≤3m) in permissiveness but applies under different conditions (existing buildings vs. length limit). (5) 15% exception for short street-level connections is unique — not found in other jurisdictions as a formal provision. Sources: DM 236/1989 §8.1.11 (bosettiegatti.eu primary text), biblus.acca.it, studiomadera.it, casaoggidomani.it. CONFIDENCE: high — DM 236/1989 art 8.1.11 text cited from multiple legal sources directly.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-11T03:10:17.461180+00:00','session_2026-05-11c-tier2-continued');
INSERT INTO "search_languages" VALUES('stair-ramp-threshold-biomechanics-accessibility','KO','SEARCHED',8,'TIER2 NATIVE SEARCH 2026-05-11. KEY INSTRUMENT: 장애인·노인·임산부 등의 편의증진 보장에 관한 법률 시행규칙 별표1 (Enforcement Rules of the Act on Ensuring Convenience for Persons with Disabilities, Annex 1). TWO-TIER by ELEMENT TYPE (unique structure): (1) External accessible pathway (접근로): standard ≤1/18 (5.56%); topographic exception ≤1/12 (8.33%). (2) Building ramp (경사로): standard ≤1/12 (8.33%); exception for existing buildings h≤1m with permanent assistance ≤1/8 (12.5%). Platform every 0.75m height change. Min width 1.2m (exception 0.9m for retrofit). CRITICAL DIVERGENCES: (1) KO distinguishes element type: external paths (≤1/18 = 5.56%) are stricter than internal ramps (≤1/12 = 8.33%). No other jurisdiction in the set has this specific distinction. (2) External path ≤1/18 (5.56%) is stricter than JA mandatory (1/12 = 8.33%), similar to FR new ERP (≤5%) and IT recommended (5-6%), and slightly less restrictive than DA/FI (≤5% = 1/20). (3) Building ramp ≤1/12 (8.33%) matches JA/ZH/ADA/SV universal values. (4) Exception 1/8 (12.5%) for existing buildings with assistance is more permissive than IT new-build (8%) but requires a permanent assistance service condition. Sources: law.go.kr/별표1, socialfocus.co.kr, 영등포구청/편의시설, qnaqc.co.kr/2015-12-18 (full legal text). CONFIDENCE: high — primary law text (별표1) retrieved from multiple official sources.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-11T03:15:46.948011+00:00','session_2026-05-11d-tier2-final');
INSERT INTO "search_languages" VALUES('stair-ramp-threshold-biomechanics-accessibility','SV','SEARCHED',7,'TIER2 NATIVE SEARCH 2026-05-11. KEY INSTRUMENT: BBR (BFS 2011:6) avsnitt 3:122, 3:142, now transitioning to BFS 2024:12. RAMP GRADIENT: Legally binding maximum (föreskrift): ≤1:12 (8.33%). General advice (allmänt råd): ≤1:20 (5%) recommended for safer use. ALM (Boverkets föreskrifter for public outdoor areas): ≤1:20 recommended. Definition: paths steeper than 5% (1:20) transition to ramp and must meet full ramp requirements (vilplan, avåkningsskydd, kontrastmarkering). Threshold: tröskel/niveaufri approach. Minimum ramp width: 1.30m. CRITICAL DIVERGENCE from DE: SV binding max 1:12 (8.33%) is less strict than DE''s 6% mandatory limit; SV recommended 1:20 equals DE''s general limit. Two-tier structure (binding/recommended) absent in DE (single value). CRITICAL DIVERGENCE from UK: UK uses length-tiered table; SV uses single mandatory maximum (1:12) + single recommendation (1:20). CRITICAL DIVERGENCE from NO: NO general 1:15 is between SV binding 1:12 and SV recommended 1:20. Sources: Boverket PBL kunskapsbanken (boverket.se/ramper), Västra Götaland riktlinjer, Arbetsmiljöverket. CONFIDENCE: high — Boverket is primary regulatory source.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-11T02:39:49.184428+00:00','session_2026-05-11a-tier2-multilingual');
INSERT INTO "search_languages" VALUES('stair-ramp-threshold-biomechanics-accessibility','NL','SEARCHED',8,'TIER2 NATIVE SEARCH 2026-05-11. KEY INSTRUMENTS: Bouwbesluit 2012 (current to Jan 2024, now replaced by Bbl/Besluit bouwwerken leefomgeving). Current Bbl (in force since Jan 2024, updated July 2025): Article 4.30 hellingbaan (ramp). RAMP GRADIENT — HEIGHT-TIERED table (UNIQUE STRUCTURE — no other jurisdiction in set uses this): h>0.5m: ≤1:20 (5%); h 0.25-0.5m: ≤1:16 (6.25%); h≤0.25m: ≤1:12 (8.33%). Bbl July 2025 addition: h≤5cm: ≤1:6 (16.7%); h 5-10cm: ≤1:10 (10%); h 10-25cm: ≤1:12 (8.33%). Width ≥1.1m. Max height ≤1m (above 1m, lifts required). Rest platforms required at top and bottom. CRITICAL DIVERGENCES: (1) NL uses HEIGHT-TIERED table (gradient based on height difference) vs. UK/ES/FR using LENGTH-TIERED (gradient based on run length) vs. DA/FI/IT using single values. This is a fundamentally different design philosophy. (2) For large height differences (>0.5m), NL requires 1:20 (same as DA/FI and FR new-build standard). (3) For small height differences (≤25cm), NL allows 1:12 (8.33%) — same as JA/ZH/ADA universal. (4) NL IT standard (Integrale Toegankelijkheids standard) as non-binding complement gives ≥1:25 as "flat" (no gradient requirements), consistent with Bouwbesluit. Sources: bwtinfo.nl, handelbouwadvies.nl/toegankelijkheidssector, iplo.nl, berkela.home.xs4all.nl/Bouwbesluit-2000 (primary text). CONFIDENCE: high — primary Bouwbesluit article text cited.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-11T03:15:46.948011+00:00','session_2026-05-11d-tier2-final');
INSERT INTO "search_languages" VALUES('stair-ramp-threshold-biomechanics-accessibility','PT','SEARCHED',7,'TIER2 NATIVE SEARCH 2026-05-11. KEY INSTRUMENT: Decreto-Lei n.º 163/2006, de 8 de agosto (accessibility legal regime), normas técnicas §2.5.1. RAMP GRADIENT — TWO-CONDITION TABLE (slope + height + length simultaneously constrained): (1) Standard: inclinação ≤6%, height ≤0.6m, horizontal projection ≤10m; (2) Short run: inclinação ≤8%, height ≤0.4m, horizontal projection ≤5m. Curved ramps: ≤8%; the 10%/12% tolerances do NOT apply to curved ramps (§2.5.3). Min width 1.2m. APD advocacy position: stricter ≤6% universal (current law not yet amended). CRITICAL DIVERGENCES: (1) PT primary standard ≤6% matches DE''s general mandatory (6%) and is stricter than IT/JA/ZH/ADA (8-8.33%). (2) PT constrains slope, height, AND horizontal projection simultaneously — no other jurisdiction requires all three simultaneously. Most jurisdictions constrain slope + one other parameter. (3) No exception for existing buildings in primary §2.5.1 (unlike IT which allows 12% retrofit). (4) PT''s 8% exception (h≤0.4m, proj≤5m) is identical to FR''s short-run tolerance condition. Sources: doutorfinancas.pt/DL163-2006 (partial text), acessibilidade-portugal.blogspot.com, vidaacessivel.pt/rampas, apd.org.pt. CONFIDENCE: high for 6%/8% values and conditions; medium for absence of specific retrofit exception (may exist in DL 163/2006 later amendments not retrieved).','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-11T03:15:46.948011+00:00','session_2026-05-11d-tier2-final');
INSERT INTO "search_languages" VALUES('stair-ramp-threshold-biomechanics-accessibility','NO','SEARCHED',7,'TIER2 NATIVE SEARCH 2026-05-11. KEY INSTRUMENT: TEK17 §8-6. RAMP GRADIENT: general access routes must not exceed 1:15 (stigning ikke brattere enn 1:15); exception for stretches up to 5m: 1:12 permitted. If terrain prevents 1:15, maximum 1:10. Horizontal rest areas (hvileplan): minimum 1.6m×1.6m every 1.0m of height difference. Free width: minimum 1.8m (except stretches ≤5m: minimum 1.4m). Cross-fall: maximum 1:50. THRESHOLD: trinnfri (step-free) required. CRITICAL DIVERGENCE from DE: NO general limit 1:15 vs DE 6% (1:16.67) — essentially the same (≈6.67% vs 6%) with slight DE advantage. Exception: NO allows 1:12 for ≤5m vs DE 10% for ≤3m — DE allows steeper exception for shorter runs. CRITICAL DIVERGENCE from UK: NO has a single general maximum (1:15) vs UK''s length-tiered table; UK''s 1:15 is for 5m runs only. Source: DiBK (dibk.no §8-6), from earlier session search [search result 25]. CONFIDENCE: high — DiBK is primary regulatory source.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-11T02:38:32.334911+00:00','session_2026-05-11a-tier2-multilingual');
INSERT INTO "search_languages" VALUES('stair-ramp-threshold-biomechanics-accessibility','JA','SEARCHED',9,'TIER2 NATIVE SEARCH 2026-05-11. KEY INSTRUMENTS: バリアフリー法 (高齢者、障害者等の移動等の円滑化の促進に関する法律, Barrier-Free Promotion Act). Two-tier standard: (1) 移動等円滑化基準 (mandatory minimum); (2) 移動等円滑化誘導基準 (guidance/desirable). RAMP GRADIENT — Mandatory (基準): ≤1/12 (8.33%), width ≥120cm, rest platforms every ≤75cm height. Exception: h≤16cm, slope ≤1/8 (12.5%). Guidance (誘導): ≤1/12 mandatory, width ≥150cm. RECOMMENDED (望ましい): outdoor ≤1/15 (6.7%); best practice ≤1/20 (5%). THRESHOLD: height difference >2cm requires a ramp. CRITICAL DIVERGENCE: (1) JA uses single mandatory max (1/12 = 8.33%), not length-tiered like UK — but stricter than ADA''s 1:12 implied universality in practice due to exception system. (2) JA mandatory 1/12 is LESS strict than DE''s 6% (1:16.67): DE does not allow ramps steeper than 6% in most cases. (3) JA has indoor/outdoor distinction (outdoor preferred ≤1/15 vs indoor ≤1/12). (4) Small height exception (h≤16cm → ≤1/8) allows steeper than any other jurisdiction''s standard case. Sources: barrierfree.t-life.co.jp, kenchiku-setsubi.biz (バリアフリー法 gradient table), MLIT checklist (mlit.go.jp/07-01yuudou.pdf), note.com/ura410 (一級建築士 exam source confirming values). CONFIDENCE: high — multiple Japanese architect/building professional sources confirm these values from the primary law.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-11T02:55:46.554597+00:00','session_2026-05-11b-tier2-continued');
