Per-source post-hoc characterization: French Snoezelen practice is predominantly practitioner-mediated (accompagnateur controls stimuli) and has a registered trademark, both diverging from BPC''s user-control framing.','FR primary: ''Snoezelen autisme efficacité'' | FR adversarial: ''Snoezelen autisme critique limitation evidence cost-effectiveness''',NULL,'French-language review on Snoezelen efficacy. Key finding: 41.7% of included studies reported unfavorable cost-effectiveness. Notes Snoezelen is a registered trademark (marque déposée). Found via multilingual remediation search.
[2026-05-11] Verified via CrossRef bibliographic search 2026-05-11 (CONFIRMED). Médecine 2022 journal (John Libbey Eurotext). Title and year match. Authors not in CrossRef metadata.','2026-05-10 13:43:44','session_2026-05-10b-multilingual-sensory','2026-05-12 21:14','session_2026-05-12j-phase-b-verification',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'316-323',9,NULL,'journal-article',0,NULL,NULL,NULL);

Per-source post-hoc characterization: Chinese SI training model is practitioner-directed; user control is absent from the discourse. Genuine paradigm divergence, not translation gap.','ZH primary: ''感觉统合训练 自闭症 房间 设计'' | ZH adversarial: ''感觉统合 自闭症 批评 局限 证据 中国''',NULL,'SR+MA focusing on Chinese children with ASD receiving SI intervention. Key context: Chinese ASD prevalence 0.7% among school-aged (6-12), ~700,000 affected. Found via multilingual remediation search.
[2026-05-11] Verified via CrossRef bibliographic search 2026-05-11 (CONFIRMED). Frontiers in Psychiatry 2025 — Lyu et al. systematic review on SI for autistic Chinese children. PMC ID may differ from DB note (DB said PMC12673401) — DOI verified.','2026-05-10 13:44:34','session_2026-05-10b-multilingual-sensory','2026-05-12 21:14','session_2026-05-12j-phase-b-verification',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'1623149',11,NULL,'journal-article',2,NULL,NULL,NULL);

Per-source post-hoc characterization: Korean SI is therapist-directed (일대일 치료 = one-to-one therapy). Korean SR calls for higher quality evidence; user control absent.','KO primary: ''감각통합 자폐 방 설계'' | KO adversarial: ''감각통합 자폐 비판 한계 근거''',NULL,'Korean SR: 10 studies, all showed positive SI effects on ASD children. BUT: predominantly single-subject designs (not RCTs); calls for higher quality evidence. Measures used: Sensory Profile + COPM. Covers clinical intervention, NOT room design or user control.
[2026-05-11] Verified via CrossRef bibliographic search 2026-05-11 (PROBABILISTIC). CrossRef returned Jung (2014) ''A Systematic Review on Effects of School-Based Occupational Therapy'' DOI:10.18064/jkasi.2014.12.1.025 as top match. May not be the exact paper the DB note ''국내 자폐스펙트럼장애 아동 감각통합 중재방법'' refers to. Held without DOI assignment pending owner spot-check.','2026-05-10 13:45:35','session_2026-05-10b-multilingual-sensory','2026-05-12 21:14','session_2026-05-12j-phase-b-verification',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'48-59',12,NULL,'journal-article',0,NULL,NULL,NULL);

Per-source post-hoc characterization: McKee 2007 (cited via VISS Skanderborg) found NO evidence for Snoezelen in autism and examples of behavior worsening. Directly contests BPC.','DA primary: ''sansestimulation Snoezelen autisme'' | DA adversarial: ''Snoezelen autisme kritik begrænsning evidens'' (cited via VISS Skanderborg practice critique)',NULL,'ADVERSARIAL: Found no evidence to support Snoezelen for autism; examples of behavior worsening. Cited in Danish VISS knowledge center review. Directly challenges BPC prior.
[2026-05-11] Verified via CrossRef bibliographic search 2026-05-11 (CONFIRMED). Research in Developmental Disabilities 28(3):304-316. Title in DB (''disturbing behaviour'') was an approximate description, not exact title.','2026-05-10 14:01:19','session_2026-05-10b-multilingual-sensory','2026-05-12 21:14','session_2026-05-12j-phase-b-verification',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'304-316',5,'en','journal-article',32,NULL,NULL,NULL);

Per-source post-hoc characterization: Lotan & Gold 2009 meta-analysis on Snoezelen for ID (PROXY population) found no significant effect. Undermines broader Snoezelen evidence base.','Cross-language adversarial pull (DA + EN MA search): ''Snoezelen meta-analysis intellectual disability effectiveness''',NULL,'ADVERSARIAL: Found NO significant effect of Snoezelen for persons with intellectual disabilities. Cited in VISS Skanderborg and Swedish OT thesis. Challenges the evidence base, though population is ID not autism-specific.
[2026-05-11] Verified via CrossRef bibliographic search 2026-05-11 (CONFIRMED). J Intellect Dev Disabil 34(3):207-215. Verified.','2026-05-10 14:01:19','session_2026-05-10b-multilingual-sensory','2026-05-12 21:14','session_2026-05-12j-phase-b-verification',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
CREATE TABLE "evidence_sources_v1_legacy" (
    ref_id              TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
    authors             TEXT NOT NULL,
    year                TEXT,
    title               TEXT NOT NULL,
    doi                 TEXT,
    doi_less_key        TEXT,
    pmid                TEXT,
    tier                INTEGER CHECK(tier IS NULL OR tier BETWEEN 1 AND 6),
    evidence_type       TEXT,
    jurisdiction        TEXT,
    metadata_quality    TEXT
                        CHECK(metadata_quality IN (
                            'COMPLETE','PMID-ONLY','GREY','AUTHOR-TITLE-ONLY'
                        )),
    verification_status TEXT,
    co1_provenance      TEXT,
    co1_source_type     TEXT,
    synthesis_attribution_required INTEGER CHECK(
        synthesis_attribution_required IN (0,1)
    ),
    notes               TEXT,
    created_at          TEXT NOT NULL,
    created_by_session  TEXT NOT NULL,
    updated_at          TEXT NOT NULL,
    updated_by_session  TEXT NOT NULL
, derivation_chain TEXT, prior_expectation TEXT, search_queries_used TEXT, doi_resolution_outcome TEXT);
