STANDARD: 《老年人照料设施建筑设计标准》 — Chinese building standard for elderly care facility design (EXISTS, not "developing" as previously noted). JGJ 450 governs indoor environmental standards including temperature for care facilities. GB 50763 for accessibility.

认知障碍友好环境 (cognitive-friendly environment) standards: 小规模组团式平面布局 8-20人 (small-group unit layout 8-20 persons). Specific requirements: 去机构化和去商业化 (de-institutionalization), natural ventilation and daylight mandatory for living spaces.

ADVERSARIAL: Public activity spaces in Chinese care facilities often lack natural ventilation and daylight — "公共活动厅朝北" (activity rooms facing north) causing drowsiness in dementia residents. Thermal comfort interacts with daylight/ventilation design. Standard GB approach to HVAC treats temperature in isolation from circadian/ventilation needs.

CORRECTION: Prior batch note said "Chinese elderly care facility standards developing. GB standards reference general HVAC." This was WRONG — specific standards exist (JGJ 450, 老年人照料设施建筑设计标准). The note was based on general knowledge, not ZH-language search.

CROSS-JURISDICTIONAL SYNTHESIS:
- PMV-PPD not validated for elderly populations.
- "Symptomless cooling" documented in EN literature.
- ZH uniquely integrates thermal/ventilation/daylight as linked design variables for cognitive care.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-10 22:24','session_2026-05-10f-term-alias-expansion');

