- ADA 20% rule: Alterations capped at 20% of project cost for path-of-travel.
ADVERSARIAL:
- "<1%" applies ONLY to new construction. Retrofit costs dramatically higher ($1.50-$9.00/sqft per RHFAC).
- Schroeder & Steinfeld 1979 is 45+ years old — construction costs/methods radically changed.
- No peer-reviewed meta-analysis of accessibility construction cost premiums exists.
- "New build vs retrofit" is fundamental confound in all cost claims.
- Cost estimates methodology-dependent: what counts as "accessibility cost" vs "good design" is subjective.
