STANDARD: 光警報装置の設置に係るガイドライン (FDMA Light Alarm Device Installation Guideline) — established 2016 by 総務省消防庁 (FDMA), revised 2025 (消防予第30号 令和7年1月30日). This is a DETAILED national guideline that the prior batch note completely missed.

Key requirements:
- 0.4 lm/m² minimum illuminance across coverage area
- Specified facility types: large airports/stations (令別表第一(10)項), facilities mainly used by hearing-impaired persons (令別表第一(6)項ロ・ハ), other facilities where active fire notification is deemed necessary
- Effective coverage must not span 2+ floors and must respect compartment boundaries (floor/wall/door)
- Cannot substitute for required acoustic alarms — light alarms are SUPPLEMENTARY

CORRECTION: Prior batch note said "Japanese fire service law has strobe requirements, no JA research on seizure interaction found." This was WRONG twice over — (1) the requirements are in a 消防庁 GUIDELINE not 消防法 itself, and (2) Japan has explicitly studied effectiveness via FDMA proof-of-concept at 7 medical/airport/welfare facilities with 71 hearing-impaired subjects and 90 staff (平成25年度 effectiveness verification).

ADVERSARIAL: JA standard does NOT specify flash frequency limits for photosensitive epilepsy. Standard focuses on illuminance and coverage, not biological safety. No JA-language research found on JA-specific seizure interaction with these devices.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-11 01:20','session_2026-05-10f-term-alias-expansion');

STANDARD: DIN/TS 67600:2022 — "Biologically effective illumination: design guidelines" — ONLY mandatory-track national standard for circadian lighting globally. References CIE S 026 melanopic EDI.
ADVERSARIAL: DIN/TS 67600 is a Technical Specification (TS), not a full DIN standard — lower normative weight. Still not incorporated into mandatory building codes (Arbeitsstättenrichtlinien). Practical implementation limited by luminaire orientation (horizontal vs vertical plane issue).
PROTOCOL COMPLIANCE: FULL — standard + adversarial searched, protocol fields populated.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-10T21:19:26Z','session_2026-05-10e-slug3-adversarial');

STANDARD: Interact/Signify article describes WELL L01-L03 in French. Filière 3e trade journal promotes circadian lighting. NF EN 12464-1 referenced for traditional illuminance but does NOT include melanopic EDI requirements. No French building code mandates circadian/melanopic lighting.

ADVERSARIAL: Brown 2022 (PMC8929548) itself acknowledges "uncertainty as to whether [melanopsin-based photometric quantity] provides a sufficiently detailed model." PMC7970181: "effects often confounded by interindividual variations in sensitivity to light." MedRxiv preprint: "whether melanopic EDI provides superior predictive value... in the real-world is not yet established."

KEY FINDING: Brown 2022 consensus recommends ≥250 melanopic EDI. BPC item B-01 specifies ≥150 EML. The BPC uses the older metric (EML vs melanopic EDI) AND a lower threshold (150 vs ~275 EML equivalent).

