Chile Ley de Autismo N°21.545 requires schools to adapt spaces for ASD inclusion. Spanish academia: "Arquitectura Sensorial y Autismo" study on preschool classroom parameters. Sala multisensorial in schools growing. CTE DB SUA does not address autism. Mostafa ASPECTSS Index referenced in Spanish-language literature.
ADVERSARIAL SEARCHED: "escuela autismo diseño crítica limitación evidencia inclusión"
FINDINGS:
- Chile Red Espectro Autista 2023: 60%+ families report school crises due to inadequate support
- Chile University 2024: 45% of autistic students experienced physical restraint during crises
- Evidence supports DUA (Universal Design for Learning) including "aulas silenciosas," pictograms, flexible timing
- Spanish/Latin American literature focuses on pedagogical inclusion, not architectural specs
- No CTE standard for autism school design
ADVERSARIAL VALUE: ES literature frames sensory regulation as part of DUA, not specific architectural specifications. No evidence for NC-25 or NRC thresholds.
