Chu & Lee 2023 (PeerJ CS): educational space optimization for autistic children via deep learning — notes Chinese research on indoor space for autism "still in its infancy." RCT in Chinese special education schools (NCT07277101) tests sensory-friendly PE adjusting noise/light. Indoor lighting/color SLR (PMC12715023) notes critical appraisal gaps. No GB standard for autism school design.
ADVERSARIAL SEARCHED: "自闭症 学校设计 批评 局限 证据 中国"
FINDINGS:
- Deng & Yan 2017 (中国特殊教育): Critical reflection on EBP in autism — challenges uncritical Western import. EBP focuses on "quantifiable short-term behavioral goals" ignoring long-term psychological/social development.
- Only ~10% of Chinese autistic children in inclusive education (Censo 2023)
- China Disability Federation: existing educational environments "unsuitable" but focus on pedagogy not architecture
- No GB standard for autism school design
ADVERSARIAL VALUE: Chinese academic criticism of Western EBP framework itself. No ZH evidence for architectural specifications.
PROTOCOL COMPLIANCE: FULL — standard + adversarial searched, protocol fields populated.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-10T20:36:02Z','session_2026-05-10e-slug3-adversarial');

De Domenico 2024 pilot RCT on MSE in Italian ASD context. Italian scoping review on built environment and ASD (PMC8003767) identifies sensory quality, intelligibility, predictability as 3 key factors. No UNI standard for autism school design.
ADVERSARIAL SEARCHED: (IT covered via PMC8003767 + English-language searches)
FINDINGS:
- Tola et al. 2021 (University of Sassari, PMC8003767, DOI:10.3390/ijerph18063203): Built Environment Design and ASD Scoping Review. Only 21/801 studies met criteria — "relatively limited." Three factors: sensory quality, intelligibility, predictability. Almost exclusively school children, not adults. No urban environment studies.
- Abdelmoula et al. 2024 (PMC11860188): Confirms ASPECTSS as only evidence-based framework
- European Journal of Public Health 2020 scoping review: "almost exclusively focus on closed/dedicated spaces"
- No UNI standard for autism school design
ADVERSARIAL VALUE: Italian scoping review confirms THIN evidence base (21/801). Three-factor model (sensory/intelligibility/predictability) is broader than noise+visual. No specific thresholds.
PROTOCOL COMPLIANCE: FULL — standard + adversarial searched, protocol fields populated.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-10T20:36:02Z','session_2026-05-10e-slug3-adversarial');

Chu & Lee 2023 (Kookmin Univ Seoul) educational space optimization. Korean accessibility focused on physical mobility. No KS standard for autism school design. Thin Korean-language evidence base.
ADVERSARIAL SEARCHED: "자폐 학교환경 비판 한계 근거 포용교육"
FINDINGS:
- Korean Wikipedia: Creating environments that SEPARATE autistic/neurotypical students → social isolation long-term
- Namu Wiki: ABA criticized as human rights violation; autism rights activists argue behavioral modification is discrimination
- PMC11653068 Editorial: Korean-context study on stigma leading to bullying, trauma, exclusion
